<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1195] Allow datastore function as query expression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1195</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Create a query expression that uses a datastore function such as MOD(..) or MAX(..) in a generic fashion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is required by function() support for CriteriaQuery and adds a generic capability for queries so we can query something like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &quot;select  CURRENT_USER(), x.name FROM Person x WHERE LENGTH(x.name)&amp;gt;10 ORDER BY LENGTH(x.name)&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Notice that JPQL Parser may not like the syntax &amp;#8211; but CriteriaQuery will allow such possibility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Allow the function() to accept 0 or more arguments as expressions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
